<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL - MAINSHAFT
        ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure the lower countershaft drive gear marked tooth is in time with main drive gear marked
                    teeth.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block the upper countershaft forward against the case wall (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m5">Figure 225</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m5" filename="../figg13/G13020m5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 225. Block Upper Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With reverse gear forward against the next speed gear and mainshaft pilot end over the
                integral oil pump gear, lower the mainshaft assembly while pulling shaft rear through the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m5">Figure 225</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the input shaft forward until the drive gear is against the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m6">Figure 226</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m6" filename="../figg13/G13020m6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 226. Drive Gear Against Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After the mainshaft drops into the case, slide the countershaft back and the mainshaft
                should fall down between the countershafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m6">Figure 226</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the mainshaft pilot-end into the input shaft pilot bushing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m6">Figure 226</hotlnk>). Mesh the mainshaft gears with the corresponding
                countershaft assembly gears.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the upper reverse idler gear in the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m7">Figure 227</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m7" filename="../figg13/G13020m7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 227. Position Upper Reverse Idler Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mesh the reverse gear teeth with the reverse idler gear teeth and move the reverse gear to
                the rear as far as possible (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m7">Figure 227</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the reverse gear spacer external splines with the reverse gear and move the spacer
                into the reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m8">Figure 228</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m8" filename="../figg13/G13020m8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 228. Align Splines</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the reverse gear I.D. snap ring and move the reverse gear forward on the mainshaft
                and against the reverse gear limit washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m8">Figure 228</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To finish the input shaft/front bearing cover installation, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s13020_HL1302007.xml" xrefid="hl1302007">INPUT SHAFT</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
